{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859521700,"sessionID":"ses_28689d81bffeoSw6AycaOV3rq3","part":{"id":"prt_d7979d384001KKaueyaIX9Mi5F","messageID":"msg_d7979bdf50014lATtxO9VcHPnW","sessionID":"ses_28689d81bffeoSw6AycaOV3rq3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 (Router Session Management)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement session management functionality in `pkg/router` to handle the complete lifecycle of sessions between clients and sandbox instances. The Session Manager serves as the bridge between incoming HTTP requests and sandbox instances, integrating with the Kubernetes API via client-go to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, maintaining session state in the session store, and ensuring proper session affinity for routing.\n6: \n7: The Session Manager handles four primary responsibilities:\n8: 1. **Session Resolution**: Maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints using the session store with fallback to Kubernetes resource lookup\n9: 2. **Session Lifecycle**: Manages session creation, updates, expiration, and cleanup through the store interface\n10: 3. **Session Affinity**: Ensures consistent routing of requests to the same sandbox instance within a session\n11: 4. **Resource Integration**: Uses client-go to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: ### In scope\n18: \n19: | Item | Detail |\n20: |------|--------|\n21: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` |\n22: | **Core functionality** | Session creation, resolution, state tracking, lifecycle management, affinity routing |\n23: | **Integration with** | Session store (Redis/Valkey), Kubernetes API via client-go (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter), Workload Manager |\n24: | **Protocols** | HTTP session headers (`x-agentcube-session-id`), WebSocket session tracking |\n25: | **CRD Types** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1.AgentRuntime`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` |\n26: | **Configuration** | Session timeouts, TTL defaults, cleanup intervals via config |\n27: | **Observability** | Session metrics (active sessions, creation rate, expiration), structured logging |\n28: \n29: ### Out of scope\n30: \n31: - HTTP reverse proxy implementation (handled by AR-009)\n32: - JWT signing and authentication (handled by AR-009)\n33: - TLS termination (handled by AR-009)\n34: - Direct sandbox pod management (handled by Workload Manager)\n35: - Multi-cluster session replication (single cluster scope)\n36: - Session state persistence beyond store TTL (ephemeral session model)\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## Design\n41: \n42: ### File layout\n43: \n44: | File | Role |\n45: |------|------|\n46: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | **NEW** — SessionManager interface and core implementation |\n47: | `pkg/router/session_store.go` | **NEW** — Store-backed session persistence layer |\n48: | `pkg/router/session_resolver.go` | **NEW** — Session-to-sandbox resolution logic |\n49: | `pkg/router/session_lifecycle.go` | **NEW** — Session creation, expiration, cleanup handlers |\n50: | `pkg/router/session_affinity.go` | **NEW** — Session affinity and sticky routing logic |\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 657. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 (Router Session Management)\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement session management functionality in `pkg/router` to handle the complete lifecycle of sessions between clients and sandbox instances. The Session Manager serves as the bridge between incoming HTTP requests and sandbox instances, integrating with the Kubernetes API via client-go to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, maintaining session state in the session store, and ensuring proper session affinity for routing.\n\nThe Session Manager handles four primary responsibilities:\n1. **Session Resolution**: Maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints using the session store with fallback to Kubernetes resource lookup\n2. **Session Lifecycle**: Manages session creation, updates, expiration, and cleanup through the store interface\n3. **Session Affinity**: Ensures consistent routing of requests to the same sandbox instance within a session\n4. **Resource Integration**: Uses client-go to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775859521688,"end":1775859521698}}}}
